{
  "text": "EPC culture assay and BM-derived EPC culture was performed as described previously. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Details are provided in the online data supplement (#3). Briefly, cultured EPCs were quantified by counting the total number in 500 L of peripheral blood and averaged. EPCs isolated from BM were used for cell function assay, cell transfusion study, Western blot, and real-time PCR analysis. All cells for in vitro study were obtained from db/m, db/db, or thrombospondin (TSP)-1 \u03ea/\u03ea mice.",
